      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Monica" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Monica" href="/user/show/7313484-monica">Monica</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780983368410" href="/book/show/12672567-sliding-beneath-the-surface">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7313484-monica?shelf=books-i-won">books-i-won</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7313484-monica?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7313484-monica?shelf=books-i-have">books-i-have</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer305514962" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3502808008776129959">I won this book through a Goodreads book giveaway contest--thank you Doug Dillon and Old St. Augustine Publications!<br/><br/>Overall, I thought this book was fairly well written. I liked Jeff Golden as a main character, but I especially liked Carla Rodriguez. She&apos;s...spunky. Yeah, I think that&apos;s the word for it :) Anyways, Dillon wove together a mix of adventure and mystery to create Jeff&apos;s story. I mostly recommend this book to middle grade/younger teens and ayone who likes paranormal stories.<br/><br/><br/>***I reluc</span>
  <span id="freeText3502808008776129959" style="display:none">I won this book through a Goodreads book giveaway contest--thank you Doug Dillon and Old St. Augustine Publications!<br /><br />Overall, I thought this book was fairly well written. I liked Jeff Golden as a main character, but I especially liked Carla Rodriguez. She's...spunky. Yeah, I think that's the word for it :) Anyways, Dillon wove together a mix of adventure and mystery to create Jeff's story. I mostly recommend this book to middle grade/younger teens and ayone who likes paranormal stories.<br /><br /><br />***I reluctantly gave this book 3 stars, though I feel it deserves more. It's just my opinion. It's not the book or story, it's just that I'm not into a lot of the spiritual-ish paranormal stuff genre. But please don't let this stop you! </span>
